  "framework_note": "comp-036 reframes the comp-033 decision rule from 'plasma Cmax vs anakinra 1.5 ug/mL' to 'receptor-occupancy fraction over the 0-72h gout flare window'. The receptor-occupancy framing is the clinically-relevant metric: IL-1Ra is a competitive antagonist at IL-1R1 with Kd ~1 nM (Arend 1990 JCI; Schreuder 1997 Nature). What determines clinical efficacy is sustained competitive displacement of IL-1beta from the receptor over the flare window, not raw plasma concentration matching to anakinra. This reframe is the load-bearing methodological correction in comp-036.",
