    "cumulative_over_years_at_5_flares_yr": {
      "comment": "For a typical operator-profile patient (Brian, currently affected): 3-6 flares/year, 30+ year disease horizon. Cumulative burden axes that matter at year 5, year 10, year 20.",
      "anakinra": "~50-150 cumulative SC injections/year/decade; ADAs may rise but typically don't drive efficacy loss at acute-only dosing; injection-site fatigue probable; no characterized severe long-term toxicity.",
      "canakinumab": "~5-10 SC injections/year over decades; cumulative immunosuppressive windows ~3-12 months/year; long-term infection-risk profile not characterized at this duty cycle; cost is the practical limit.",
      "prednisone": "~5 flares/year x ~240 mg = ~1,200 mg/year x 30 years = ~36 g cumulative prednisone. Crosses bone-density threshold (typically ~2-5 g cumulative) within 2-4 years; cataract threshold typically ~10 g cumulative; adrenal-axis suppression becomes physiology; this is the durable-toxicity profile the operator is currently accepting.",
      "inhaled_mrna_repeat_dose_projected": "~15-50 inhaled mRNA-LNP exposures/year x decades = unknown cumulative anti-PEG/innate-immune profile; mRNA vaccine literature (multi-booster cohort tracking) is the closest proxy and suggests acceptable safety at 5+ exposures over 3 years; the inhaled-route and per-session-dose are larger than vaccine boosters, so direct extrapolation has uncertainty; **this is the load-bearing unknown that comp-036 cannot resolve and that wet-lab Phase 1 would need to address.**"
    }
  },
  "clinical_handoff": {
    "if_GREEN_phase_1_design": "Phase 1 dose-finding: inhaled mRNA-IL-1Ra at 4, 10, 24 mg per dose, with anakinra 100 mg SC QD x 5 days as active comparator. Primary endpoint: plasma IL-1Ra Cmax + AUC vs anakinra; pharmacodynamic endpoint: plasma IL-6 / CRP suppression in MSU-induced flare or PMA-stimulated PBMC ex vivo IL-1beta release assay. N=30-45 healthy volunteers (15/arm x 3 dose levels). Wet-lab measurement that would tighten the comp-036 verdict the most: actual translation-efficiency mass ratio (protein / mRNA delivered) in human alveolar epithelium \u2014 currently the dominant sensitivity driver (Spearman rho = +0.78 in single-dose; persists in repeat-dose).",
    "if_YELLOW_wet_lab_priority": "Single critical wet-lab measurement: actual integrated translation-efficiency mass ratio in human alveolar epithelium for inhaled m1Psi-mRNA-LNP IL-1Ra. The 1,000-50,000 ng/ug prior is the dominant uncertainty. A direct measurement in a ferret or NHP single-dose inhaled-LNP study would either confirm GREEN or tip to RED.",
    "if_RED_next_route": "Pivot to intra-articular mRNA-IL-1Ra (sister architecture to comp-035 intra-articular uricase + catalase). Local concentration at the affected joint bypasses systemic dilution; receptor-occupancy math at the joint with bolus IA mRNA delivery is fundamentally different and likely far more favorable. Alternative: accept sub-anakinra exposure with 50-3000x cost edge over canakinumab (per comp-033 economics) and target patients with prednisone-side-effect-driven need for steroid-sparing therapy even at imperfect IL-1 blockade."
  }
